Q: When folded into two equal halves a rectangular sheet had a perimeter of 48cm for each part folded along one set of sides and the same is 66cm when folded along the other set of sides. Find the area of the sheet.
Options: (a) 1584 (b) 1120 (c) 792 (d) 1320 (e) 1200
A:
 Let the length of the sheet be x. Then, the breadth of the sheet is 48-x. The perimeter of the sheet is 2(48-x) + 2x = 96. x = 24. The area of the sheet is 24*24 = 576. So the answer is (c).

